halibut
------------------------------------------
Halibut is a documentation production system, with elements similar to TeX,
debiandoc-sgml, TeXinfo, and others. It is primarily targeted at people
producing software manuals.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.44-1
  cmake-3.28.3-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  ninja-1.12.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/halibut/

Canonical download:
  https://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/halibut/halibut-1.3/halibut-1.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack halibut-1.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./halibut-1.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/halibut-1.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/halibut-1.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(halibut)
  /usr/bin/halibut.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/halibut.README
  /usr/share/doc/halibut/IndexPage.html
  /usr/share/doc/halibut/LICENCE
  /usr/share/doc/halibut/index.html
  /usr/share/doc/halibut/input.html
  /usr/share/doc/halibut/intro.html
  /usr/share/doc/halibut/licence.html
  /usr/share/doc/halibut/manpage.html
  /usr/share/doc/halibut/output.html
  /usr/share/doc/halibut/running.html
  /usr/share/info/halibut.info-1.gz
  /usr/share/info/halibut.info-2.gz
  /usr/share/info/halibut.info-3.gz
  /usr/share/info/halibut.info-4.gz
  /usr/share/info/halibut.info.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/halibut.1.gz

